%N A002875 Number of partitions of {1..3n} that are invariant under a permutation consisting of n 3-cycles with k orbits of blocks, maximized over k.
%D A002875 N. J. A. Sloane, A Handbook of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1973 (includes this sequence).
%D A002875 N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
%H A002875 Victor Meally, <a href="/A002868/a002868.pdf">Comparison of several sequences given in Motzkin's paper "Sorting numbers for cylinders..."</a>, letter to N. J. A. Sloane, N. D.
%H A002875 T. S. Motzkin, <a href="/A000262/a000262.pdf">Sorting numbers for cylinders and other classification numbers</a>, in Combinatorics, Proc. Symp. Pure Math. 19, AMS, 1971, pp. 167-176. [Annotated, scanned copy]
%H A002875 OEIS Wiki, <a href="/wiki/Sorting_numbers">Sorting numbers</a>
%H A002875 <a href="/index/So#sorting">Index entries for sequences related to sorting</a>
%t A002875 aList[n_] := Max /@ CoefficientList[Exp[y ((Exp[3x]-1)/3 + Exp[x]-1)] + O[x]^n, {x,y}] (Range[n]-1)!;
%Y A002875 Maximum row values of A395327.
%Y A002875 Cf. A000262, A001861, A002870, A002871, A002872, A002873, A002874, A036073, A294201.
%Y A002875 A294202 has a similar definition based on partition blocks rather than their orbits.
